
## Voltolino Fontani

Voltolino Fontani (Livorno, Italia 1920-1976) was an Italian painter. He was an artist who contributed to introduce the expression Atomic age in the European culture., He was the founder of Eaismo, an artistic movement linking arts to Atomic age.
In 1948 he published “Manifesto of Eaismo”, anticipating the Manifesto of Pittura nucleare by Enrico Baj (1951), and Salvador Dalì (Manifesto mistico, 1951).

